SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA EDISON COMPANY TARIFF FOR THE SALE, ASSIGNMENT, OR TRANSFER OF TRANSMISSION RIGHTS ON NON-JURISDICTIONAL TRANSMITTING UTILITY SYSTEMS
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA EDISON COMPANY
TARIFF FOR THE SALE, ASSIGNMENT, OR TRANSFER OF TRANSMISSION RIGHTS ON NON-JURISDICTIONAL TRANSMITTING UTILITY SYSTEMS
1. General Purpose: The purpose of this tariff is to provide for the sale, assignment, or transfer of transmission rights by Southern California Edison Company ("SCE") on non-jurisdictional transmitting utility systems in which the transmission provider does not play the intermediary role in secondary market transmission transactions as contemplated under the reforms that the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("Commission") adopted in Order No. 890. 2. Duration: This tariff shall continue in effect until terminated or changed and such termination or change becomes effective in accordance with any applicable regulatory requirements. 3. Services To Be Rendered: SCE may sell, assign, or transfer to a purchaser, pursuant to an agreement negotiated between them, all or a portion of SCE's rights to the use of the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility system that SCE has reserved for its own use under a service agreement with the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility or under a service agreement it has acquired from another customer. The purchaser must be an eligible customer under the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility's open access transmission tariff or other tariffs pursuant to which the transmission rights to be transferred to the purchaser were originally obtained from the transmission provider. 4. Sale of Transmission Rights: SCE may sell transmission rights that SCE has reserved for its own use from the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility. SCE may sell, assign, or transfer such transmission rights at the price provided below. 5. Terms and Conditions: Except for price, the terms and conditions under which SCE will sell, assign, or transfer transmission rights on the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility system to a purchaser shall be the terms and conditions governing the original grant of such transmission rights by the transmission provider. 6. Compensation: SCE shall sell, assign, or transfer any transmission rights pursuant to this tariff at a price mutually agreed to between SCE and purchaser, provided, however, that SCE shall sell, assign, or transfer any transmission rights purchased under the Bonneville Power Administration open access transmission tariff ("BPA OATT") pursuant to this tariff at a price not to exceed a price permitted by the BPA OATT. 7. Modifications: SCE may unilaterally apply to the Commission or other regulatory agency having jurisdiction for a modification of this tariff under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act and the regulations promulgated thereunder. 8. Electric Quarterly Reports: In its Electric Quarterly Reports, pursuant to Commission guidance, SCE will provide to the Commission data concerning transmission capacity sales, assignments, or transfers by SCE on any non-jurisdictional transmitting utility systems to the extent such transactions are entered into pursuant to this tariff. Southern California Edison Company FERC Electric Tariff, Volume No. 10
